{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af82ce59-acfe-440e-98a6-b8e816d6c3dc","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication options (`--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example with auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --client-id <your-client-id>\n```\n\nYou can also add **JWT Bearer** auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` for custom token-based auth, or use **ASP.NET Core Identity** for local user/password management.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific auth option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f97e67e6-ff86-4618-99e8-39c01e3b77d3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":284,"requestId":"A801:155537:1673C41:18FD11C:6A051E05"},"id":"63fc84c1-2a24-4da0-8d1e-a27d6a5070ae","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:57:49.930Z","parentId":"be7f5488-15e9-4b9a-b024-9fcf2aa61cb9"}
